# Publish → JSX

**Canonical guide:** [front/docs/publish-to-jsx.md](mdc:front/docs/publish-to-jsx.md)

Before converting any `front/public/publish/*.html`:

1. Follow the checklist in that doc (CSS split → JSX → components → App.js).
2. Reuse `AppShell` / `AppHeader` / `AppFooter` — never duplicate header/footer in page JSX.
3. Output paths: `src/jsx/<Page>.jsx`, `src/public/css/<page>.css`.
4. Update `App.js` nav/view and add a row to [front/sub.md](mdc:front/sub.md).

Invoke skill: `@html-publish-to-react`
